  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Persistent insomnia is highly prevalent complaint in cancer survivors, but is seldom
      satisfactorily addressed. The adaptation to cancer care of a validated, cost-effective
      intervention may offer a practicable solution. The aim of this study was to investigate the
      clinical effectiveness of homeopathy for insomnia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
